Neurotech 411-p4240030 Kneehab Xp Right Massager
Description: The Kneehab XP is an innovative and clinically-proven device that offers Multipath NMES for quadriceps strengthening and improved knee stability. The patented Multipath(TM) stimulation technology delivers accurately coordinated quadriceps contractions to accelerate recovery so you can get back to your normal activities. Published research has shown Multipath to be more effective at restoring strength and function than standard physical therapy or standard NMES. Integrating Kneehab XP into knee care before and after surgery can help promote early quadriceps strengthening and knee stability. Candidates for Multipath NMES - presenting with disuse atrophy of the VMO/quadriceps muscles: •Pre and Post Surgical - total knee replacement •Sports Injuries - ACL, LCL, MCL, PCL repair •Degenerative Conditions - osteoarthritis •Knee Joint Conditions - patella femoral syndrome Kneehab XP simulates a natural muscle recruitment sequence. Kneehab XP incorporates a patented breakthrough stimulation technology that delivers highly focused, accurately coordinated quadriceps contractions. This technology delivers multi-directional currents designed to recruit maximum muscle fiber and trigger stronger muscle contractions resulting in earlier post surgical outcomes. Kneehab XP indications for use: •Muscle re-education of the quadriceps •Maintaining or increasing range of motion of the knee joint •Prevention or retardation of disuse atrophy in the quadriceps •Early post-surgical quadriceps strengthening and improved post-surgical knee stability secondary to quadriceps strengthening •Increasing local blood circulation •Symptomatic relief and management of chronic, intractable pain •Management of intractable pain and relief of pain associated with arthritis INCLUDES A LEFT, RIGHT, OR BOTH A LEFT AND RIGHT CONDUCTIVE GARMENT(SELECT ABOVE) AND THE NEUROTECH PLUS CONTROLLER - Everything you need to get started.

Title: Neurotech 295-P4274990 Medistim Xp Massager
Description: The MediStim® XP is a portable, digital, dual channel muscle stimulation device incorporating a comprehensive range of programs to aid in the rehabilitation process in the clinic and at home. The MediStim®XP re-educates and strengthens atrophied, weakened or immobilized muscle through Neuromuscular Electrical Stimulation (NMES) therapy and aids in the management of acute pain through Transcutaneous Electrical Nerve Stimulation (TENS).MediStim® XP was developed to prevent or slow down the atrophy or weakening of muscles often associated with reduced mobility. The device works by triggering muscles to contract and relax. Joint range of motion can also be improved. The device can be used to effectively relax muscle spasms and prevent the risk of venous thrombosis after surgery. It’s easy to use with pre-set programs.

Title: Neurotech 295-P4275206 Meditens XP Massager
Description: Medi Tens Xp Is A Dual Channel, Easy To Use, Hand-Held Unit That Can Help To Manage And Relieve Your Pain. Tens Works By Sending Comfortable, Gentle Pulses To The Nerves, Via Electrode Pads Placed On The Skin. Medi Tens Xp Provides Labour Pain Relief In 2 Ways: Medi Tens Xp For Labour Works By Gently Stimulating Your Sensory Nerves, To Suppress Or Block The Pain Signal To The Brain. When These Pain Signals Are Blocked, It Becomes More Difficult For The Brain To Register The Sensation Of Pain. This Gives Immediate Pain Relief, Allowing You To Feel The 'Tingling' Sensation From The Medi Tens Xp Rather Than The Pain Endorphin Release: Which Encourages The Release Of The Bodys Own Natural, Pain-Relieving Chemicals To Fight Pain. Medi Tens Xp For Labour Encourages The Release Of Endorphins Through A Comfortable Tapping Sensation That Results In Pain Relief Even After The Unit Is Turned Off During Labour The Medi Tens Xp Has The Added Benefit Of A Trigger Facility When The Intensity Is Increased At The Start Of Program 1, The Stimulation Causes Endorphins To Be Released Throughout Your Body. As Your Labour Progresses And The Contractions Become Stronger, We Suggest That You Use The Trigger Facility To Maximise Your Pain Management When Your Contractions Occur. When The Trigger Button Is Pressed, It Automatically Changes The Stimulation To Continuous Pain Blocking, Increasing The Output Significantly. This Delivers Maximum Pain Relief When You Require It Most.
